The [[Bayer designation]] '''η Coronae Australis''' ('''Eta Coronae Australis''') is shared by two [[star]]s, in the [[constellation]] [[Corona Australis]]: *[[Eta1 Coronae Australis|η<sup>1</sup> Coronae Australis]] *[[Eta2 Coronae Australis|η<sup>2</sup> Coronae Australis]]
{{SIA |astronomical objects}}
[[Category:Bayer objects|Coronae Australis, Eta]] [[Category:Corona Australis]]

{{orphan|date=August 2010}}

'''Harmomegathy''' is the process by which [[pollen]] grains in [[arid]] environments close off their apertures to avoid losing [[water]]. This folding of the pollen grain prevents water loss until it arrives in a wetter environment.

