{{Unreferenced|date=July 2007}}In Greek mythology, '''Kallichore''' is sometimes considered one of the [[Muse]]s, and thus a daughter of [[Zeus]] (Jupiter);  a [[scholion]] to [[Hesiod]]'s ''Works and Days'' names her.  She is better known, however, as one of the [[Nysiad]]s, [[nymph]]s who nursed [[Dionysos]].  Both the lunar crater Kallichore and Jupiter's moon [[Kallichore (moon)|Kallichore]] are named after her.

