[[File:La-lopé-gabon.jpg|thumb|[[Lopé National Park]]]]

There are 13 [[national parks]] in [[Gabon]], all created in 2002 when [[President of Gabon|President]] [[Omar Bongo]] established Gabon's [[National Agency for National Parks]] ({{lang-fr|Agence Nationale des Parcs Nationaux}}, ANPN).<ref name="Group">{{cite book|author=Oxford Business Group|title=The Report: Gabon 2011|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qm8900AFGfoC&pg=PA183|publisher=Oxford Business Group|isbn=978-1-907065-48-4|page=183}}</ref> The national parks cover 10% of the country.<ref name="Warne2003">{{cite book|author=Sophie Warne|title=Gabon, Sao Tome & Principe: The Bradt Travel Guide|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wTCyVLanWZwC&pg=PA32|date=1 November 2003|publisher=Bradt Travel Guides|isbn=978-1-84162-073-2|page=32}}</ref>

