{{short description|A narrow, southward flowing ocean current along the eastward side of the southern Philippines}}
The '''Mindanao Current''' is an [[ocean current]] along the eastward side of the southern [[Philippines]]. It is a narrow, southward flowing current starting at 14°N with 13[[Sverdrup|Sv]] increasing in strength to 33[[Sverdrup|Sv]] at 5.5°N. The current splits before the coast of south-east [[Mindanao]] where one part flows cyclonically into the [[Celebes Sea]] later feeding the [[Equatorial Counter Current|North Equatorial Counter Current]] (NECC) while another part feeds the NECC directly.<ref>{{cite journal | bibcode = 1991JGR....96.7089L | title=Observations of the Mindanao current during the Western Equatorial Pacific Ocean Circulation Study | journal=Journal of Geophysical Research | volume=96 | page=7089 | year=1991 | doi=10.1029/91jc00062}}</ref>

