{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}
The '''Sugud Islands Marine Conservation Area''' or '''SIMCA''' is a ''Category II [[Marine Protected Area|MPA]]'' in [[Beluran|Beluran district]] in [[Sabah]], [[Malaysia]], comprising [[Lankayan Island]], [[Billean Island|Billean]], [[Tegaipil Island|Tegaipil]] and surrounding waters. The government of [[Sabah]], Malaysia prohibits in the area, a total of over 463 square kilometres, all resource harvesting (including all capturing of live creatures) and charges a fee to all visitors of the area.<ref name="diveb">[http://www.diveborneo.com/locations/Lankayan.htm Lankayan Island - Dive Borneo<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050406101240/http://diveborneo.com/locations/lankayan.htm |date=6 April 2005 }}</ref><ref name="coral">[http://coral.aoml.noaa.gov/pipermail/coral-list/2004-June/001089.html [Coral-List&#93; Sugud Islands Marine Conservation Area Staff Openings<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref name="finsonline">http://finsonline.com/articles.php?issue=24&article=99. Google cache, cached 19 December 2004.</ref>

